    },
    {
      "author": "Boris Khasanov",
      "text": "Why wasn't STAMP considered as an OAM tool?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:23:03.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Adrian Farrel",
      "text": "Ask the question Boris",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:23:52.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Carolina Caeiro",
      "text": "Quan, in the OAM framework you have \"Multi-Domain Fault Isolation\" as a service, can you explain what you mean by it?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:37:49.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Cheng Li",
      "text": "+1 TO cAROLINA",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:38:35.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Cheng Li",
      "text": "Carolina",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:38:47.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Quan Xiong",
      "text": "Fault localization through the Service OAM TRACE mode for isolating or troubleshooting fault domains. It will be clarified in next version. Thanks!",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:44:14.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Boris Khasanov",
      "text": "still :)",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:52:10.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Quan Xiong",
      "text": "Would it be better with  Fault localization across domains?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:55:27.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Carolina Caeiro",
      "text": "thanks Quan, will TRACE mode ever operate across separate administrative domains, or is it strictly intra-domain?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:56:49.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Carolina Caeiro",
      "text": "maybe intra domain Fault isolation/localization?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T12:57:30.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Quan Xiong",
      "text": "I think they are AS domains or areas within an administrative doamin.",
      "time": "2026-07-23T13:07:35.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Quan Xiong",
      "text": "intra-domain and inter-domain  Fault isolation/localization?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T13:08:01.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Adrian Farrel",
      "text": "It is unusual for one AS to be wiiling to share fault information with another AS",
      "time": "2026-07-23T13:08:59.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Quan Xiong",
      "text": "Thanks for your remind. What I want is to locate the failures in the network or in the service instances.",
      "time": "2026-07-23T13:10:55.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Adrian Farrel",
      "text": "Yeah. A layered approach",
      "time": "2026-07-23T13:11:32.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Carolina Caeiro",
      "text": "Right, gotcha. Worry the inter domain reference may sit outside of charter scope? Adrian prob best placed here to comment",
      "time": "2026-07-23T13:15:16.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Adrian Farrel",
      "text": "When is a domain not a domain?",
      "time": "2026-07-23T13:15:49.000Z"
    },
    {
      "author": "Quan Xiong",
      "text": "We may not mention the domain, just clarify failure location between the CATS-forwarders and service instances",
      "time": "2026-07-23T13:23:28.000Z"
    }
  ]
